In a phone call with Israeli Prime Minister Netanyahu, President Obama expressed the United States' support for Israel's right to self-defense against rocket attacks from Gaza. He urged Netanyahu to avoid civilian casualties and both leaders agreed that Hamas needs to stop its attacks on Israel. The President also spoke with Egyptian President Morsi and condemned the rocket fire from Gaza into Israel. They agreed on the importance of de-escalating the situation and staying in close touch. Vice President Biden also received a briefing from Prime Minister Netanyahu on the events in Gaza.